{
  "stem": "4284.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well, the problem was that the stallion, which was a very vicious but a gorgeous horse by the name of Baba Rosa, was my responsibility because the son of a gun understood German, and I was the only one that spoke the language.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So whenever I say, come here, do this, that doggone horse would understand it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, my biggest problem was to help a horse to mate is not your every day kick in the pants activity.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's dangerous.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The horse is wild.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I got repeatedly cut from the horse tail because it's as sharp as blades.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the Germans thought it was funny to have this little Jew get kicked around by the horse trying to help him to mate.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And at least it did give me one opportunity.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That horse and my other four received better food than we did.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we had access to the food, whether it were oats or some carrots, sometimes raw potatoes, whatever it is.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And you had the extra food that allowed you to survive.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The only humor that I ever encountered in four and a half years in camps was at that particular place when it was a rule that the little horses, once they were born, were not to have any water, only mother's milk.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And when nobody was looking, which sometimes was possible, all these horses were taken to the water trough, and now accompanied by the little ones.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was an enormous commo-- it was dusty.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was unbelieve-- we let the little horses drink, which of course caused them to have what the Germans thought was an epidemic of diarrhea.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Now, it wasn't done, believe me, to make fun of the Germans.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It wasn't done to have any joke or sense of humor.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
